Subject: emacsclient: cache buffer metadata
Message-Id: <8415e6108525c3f5-0-artemis@nixos-framework>
resolution: fixed

Our emacsclient tools like 'read' return a lot of metadata to the LLM, which
wastes tokens. Instead, we can keep a cache (within the JS side), and compare
the result we get from Emacs against what we have cached: things which are
unchanged can be left out of the response we give to the LLM.

That makes it much cheaper to do repeated operations on the same buffer; like
collaborative editing.
